news.title: Bombay HC directs Maharashtra govt to address understaffing in SRA & take action against illegalities
news.para: The Bombay High Court is concerned about the Slum Rehabilitation Authority's (SRA) understaffing. It directs the state government to address the issue. The court highlights rampant illegal property transfers within SRA projects. A case involving a disputed allotment letter is examined. The court questions the occupation of a building without a certificate for 15 years.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC upholds RERA order against Paratus Real Estates
news.para: The Uttarakhand High Court has supported a RERA order, instructing Paratus Real Estates to deposit 50% of the penalty before their appeal. This decision rejected the promoter's argument for a 30% deposit under the RERA Act. The court emphasized the Act's purpose to protect consumer interests in real estate, advocating for its strict interpretation.

news.title: Lodha Developers sells 24-acre land in Mumbai to STT Global Data Centres for ₹500 crore
news.para: Lodha Developers has sold over 24 acres of land in the Mumbai region to STT Global Data Centres for approximately Rs 500 crore, with the land deal already registered. This transaction follows Lodha's MoU with the Maharashtra government to establish a green integrated data centre park at Palava, projecting a Rs 30,000 crore investment and creating 6,000 jobs.

news.title: Government to fast track land ownership rights for Bengali families in Gadchiroli, Nagpur
news.para: Revenue Minister Chandrashekhar Bawankule announced the fast-tracking of land ownership rights for nearly 40,000 Bengali families in Gadchiroli, descendants of those who fled East Pakistan. The district collector has been directed to prioritize the proposal for ownership transfer, pending for decades. Drones will be used for land survey mapping, and private workers will be hired to expedite land measurement.

news.title: Illegal colony razed in Ludhiana’s Mundian Kalan area
news.para: The Ludhiana municipal corporation, following commissioner Aaditya Dachalwal's directives, demolished an illegal colony in Mundian Kalan, targeting the developer and structures. This action is part of an ongoing campaign against unauthorized construction across the city.

news.title: Surat: SUDA, JICA officials review model town planning schemes
news.para: Surat Urban Development Authority (SUDA) and JICA officials convened to assess model town planning schemes for the bullet train station area, with five schemes developed incorporating advanced urban planning concepts. TP schemes 61 and 63 have received draft approval, while scheme 61 is submitted as a Preliminary Town Planning Scheme.

news.title: Registrars may get power to verify land records before deals
news.para: The Centre's upcoming Registration Bill empowers states to establish regulations for registrars to meticulously verify land rights records, aiming to combat fraud and minimize legal disputes in property transactions. This initiative seeks to provide enhanced security for buyers and investors through thorough due diligence. The bill also promotes paperless registration and transparency, replacing the outdated 1908 Registration Act.

news.title: Allottee fails to pay auction quote price, loses Mysuru site
news.para: Mysuru Development Authority cancelled the allotment of a prime plot after the winning bidder failed to complete payment formalities despite quoting a staggering Rs 2 crore, far exceeding the base price. Simultaneously, another commercial plot sale progresses with a bidder paying 25% of their Rs 8.6 crore bid.

news.title: Prioritize patta, tax, water supply petitions: Tamil Nadu CM
news.para: Chief Minister M.K. Stalin prioritized key petitions at an Ungaludan Stalin camp, emphasizing swift resolution for vulnerable groups and time-bound disposal. He lauded the initiative for its efficient multi-service delivery. Additionally, Stalin inaugurated the Kalaignar centenary building and launched the Tamil Nadu State Highways Authority, aiming to expedite road projects and enhance infrastructure.

news.title: Pune civic body imposes fine on metro contractor for dumping debris
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) has fined a Metro rail project contractor Rs 15 lakh for illegal debris dumping near Balewadi High Street. The contractor has been instructed to pay the fine within two days and remove the debris, or face legal action. The PMRDA declined to comment, as the notice was issued to a private contractor.

news.title: Apple renews, expands office lease in Mumbai's Bandra-Kurla Complex
news.para: Apple India is solidifying its presence in Mumbai by renewing its lease for multiple floors at Maker Maxity in Bandra-Kurla Complex and expanding its office space. The iPhone maker's commitment includes a fresh lease for the 10th floor and terrace, reflecting its growing business and strategic expansion in the Indian market with a monthly rent of Rs 2.55 crore.

news.title: Catena Homes India accused of ₹25-crore swindle using fake leases
news.para: Police said three individuals identified as Naveen, Raman, and Ranjith have been arrested. Complaints registered by victims from different parts of city against company for scamming them with false promises of housing and defaulting repayments

news.title: Eight dead in 345 full or partial cessed building crashes since 2021: RTI
news.para: Mumbai witnessed 345 incidents of building collapses between 2021 and August 2025, resulting in 8 deaths. A 2020 amendment to the Mhada Act aimed to expedite redevelopment of dangerous cessed buildings, but the Bombay High Court found misuse of power in issuing redevelopment notices. The Supreme Court heard Mhada's challenge and reserved its order for September 24.

news.title: Hyderabad development body's land auctions fall flat, majority of plots go unsold
news.para: The Telangana government's effort to boost revenue through land auctions faced a setback as HMDA's recent offering of 93 plots across Hyderabad saw a lukewarm response. High upset prices, ranging from ₹35,000 to ₹1.75 lakh per square yard, and untimely scheduling were cited as reasons for the disappointing turnout, with many plots remaining unsold.

news.title: Seal remaining illegal buildings: HC to Jaipur civic body
news.para: The Rajasthan High Court has directed the state government and Jaipur Municipal Corporation (Heritage) to seal the remaining illegal commercial buildings in residential areas of the walled city, specifically on Haldiyon Ka Raasta. This order comes after the court noted that only five of the 19 identified buildings had been sealed, despite a previous order in February 2025.

news.title: After seven-year wait for flat, homebuyer wins legal battle against builders
news.para: The District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission in Chandigarh has ordered a housing group to refund Rs 2.4 lakh with 9% interest to a homebuyer, Akhil Awasthi, for failing to deliver a flat booked in 2018. The commission found the companies guilty of deficiency in service and unfair trade practices, awarding additional compensation for the complainant's losses and legal costs.

news.title: Suburban land demand soars amid rising costs in cities
news.para: As metro cities become increasingly expensive, buyers are seeking affordable horizontal development options in areas like Naugaon, Hapur, Khopoli, and Chikkaballapur. Developers are focusing on plots and farmland projects within driving distance of major cities, attracting buyers with budgets between ₹50 lakh and ₹2 crore.

news.title: TCC Concept to acquire Pepperfry in push towards digital marketplaces
news.para: Realty services company TCC Concept Ltd has signed a term sheet to acquire online furniture retailer Pepperfry Ltd, potentially gaining up to 100% ownership. The acquisition aims to strengthen TCC's e-commerce presence by integrating Pepperfry's established platform. Subject to due diligence and regulatory approvals, the deal follows Pepperfry's $375 million valuation in July 2023.

news.title: Blackstone appoints Katie Keenan as CEO of real estate income trust
news.para: Blackstone has appointed Katie Keenan as the new CEO of its real estate income trust and global head of Core+, succeeding Wesley LePatner, who tragically died in July. Keenan, a long-time leader at Blackstone, will also be replaced by Tim Johnson in her previous role. Zaneta Koplewicz has been named co-president and director of the real estate income trust.

news.title: Take action against those involved in constructing 65 illegal buildings in Kalyan-Dombivali: Deputy CM
news.para: Maharashtra's Deputy Chief Minister Eknath Shinde has mandated a rigorous investigation and legal proceedings against those responsible for constructing 65 unauthorized buildings in Kalyan-Dombivli. These buildings, deemed illegal by the High Court, face potential eviction for residents who were deceived by builders.
